    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:1.1",
          "pli": "“Dvayaṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, I will teach you a duality. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:1.2",
          "pli": "Taṃ suṇātha. ",
          "en": "Listen … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:1.3",
          "pli": "Kiñca, bhikkhave, dvayaṃ? ",
          "en": "And what is a duality? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:1.4",
          "pli": "Cakkhuñceva rūpā ca, sotañceva saddā ca, ghānañceva gandhā ca, jivhā ceva rasā ca, kāyo ceva phoṭṭhabbā ca, mano ceva dhammā ca—",
          "en": "It’s just the eye and sights, the ear and sounds, the nose and smells, the tongue and tastes, the body and touches, and the mind and thoughts. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:1.5",
          "pli": "idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dvayaṃ. ",
          "en": "This is called a duality. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:2.1",
          "pli": "Yo, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadeyya: ",
          "en": "Mendicants, suppose someone was to say: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:2.2",
          "pli": "‘ahametaṃ dvayaṃ paccakkhāya aññaṃ dvayaṃ paññapessāmī’ti, tassa vācāvatthukamevassa. ",
          "en": "‘I’ll reject this duality and describe another duality.’ They’d have no grounds for that, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:2.3",
          "pli": "Puṭṭho ca na sampāyeyya. ",
          "en": "they’d be stumped by questions, and, in addition, they’d get frustrated. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:2.4",
          "pli": "Uttariñca vighātaṃ āpajjeyya. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:2.5",
          "pli": "Taṃ kissa hetu? ",
          "en": "Why is that? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:2.6",
          "pli": "Yathā taṃ, bhikkhave, avisayasmin”ti. ",
          "en": "Because they’re out of their element.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn35.92:2.7",
          "pli": "Navamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
